.

⬇️Hey guys ⬇️

I have wanted to film and update you guys about what’s happening for a while but I’m just not ready or willing to be on camera. There’s been times in my life on social media where stuff gets hard and I just wanna retreat into myself and not be “out there”. I don’t want the pressure or the attention…I just want to exist.

At a routine doc appt in March I was told that I might have cancer. I actually went through this in 2020…which started my incredibly difficult struggle with anxiety and panic disorder…resulting in me going for in patient treatment in late 2021. I lost my mother to cancer in late 2019…so you can imagine hearing this back then was something my psyche just couldn’t handle.

I was under the impression after surgical intervention and multiple tests that I was in the clear. But unfortunately per the March 2023 appt…that is not the case.

I have had several biopsy’s…an MRI…more tests and doc visits than I care to count not to mention the fear for myself and my baby that I am carrying. Luckily I have been assured numerous times that my child is ok the concern is how to treat me and how we do this in a timely manner.

At the point we still don’t know if I actually have it…but reports are still coming back concerning…there’s just difficulty around getting the formal diagnosis until I give birth. At one point had docs telling me that I may have to deliver preterm with my child needing to spend time in the NICU. This is still not off the table but the time frame in which it might is far less scary than it was originally.

This has been a nightmare.

I feel grateful that so far we are still in the “inconclusive” stage of everything…and I have one more biopsy and a maternal fetal medicine appt to attend in the coming weeks.

I have a lot of medical anxiety without benefit of all this due to watching my mother die in 2019. It still traumatizes me to this day. 

BUT

A nurse said something to me in this process that has become my mantra. “So many things had to go RIGHT to get to this point”.

And that is something I try to think about as much as I can.

Take care of yourselves and thank you for checking on me so much.

Speak soon,
Whit xo

🥀NEW VIDEO IS LIVE 🥀
.
How do we get past our insecurities and fear of what others think to reach the next level? How many of us spend countless hours stressing about what the nameless and faceless will think of us and what we do? When will we finally be free of the constraints and expectations of people we don’t even LIKE?
.
I want to get into this today with you guys because some people I care about and think very highly of struggle with this EXACT issue, and it’s heartbreaking to watch.
.
I am human and have my areas to work on in this respect, but overall, I gave up caring what other people thought long ago. There’s no award we win at the end of our lives for always keeping everyone happy. 
.
💋 Like I say in the video… 💋 

You can’t just give anyone an audience with the queen. So choose who has access to your energy and mind very wisely. 
.
ANNOUNCEMENT: Patreon (and another exclusive membership group) will return soon! I need to get back in the swing of things, and we will be back to having exclusive live streams, a book club, and more. So stay tuned! 
.

✨ Life lately…. ✨

🥀 Invitation to get out of your head today🥀
-Unplugging 
-Take in some fresh air
-Pray
-Meditate
-Practice gratitude
-Do something kind for someone else
.
Your feminine energy is drained by over-exertion, either physically or mentally. The feminine MUST rest. Just because most of the energy you expend may be in the mental or emotional realm doesn't mean that it will not eventually exhaust you.
.
Burnout, stress, anxiety, and depression in women are at an all-time high. You will not get an award at the end of your life for refusing to take time for yourself. No gold stars are handed out for fighting everything tooth and nail all the time instead of practicing discernment and removing yourself from harmful situations. 
.
I ALWAYS tell you guys...the feminine is in flow. We flow to what feels good and away from what doesn't. 
.
Once you can change the narrative in your head placed by a society that desecrates and devalues all things feminine...you will find that life CAN be easy. It CAN be beautiful, fulfilling, and free. 
.
I feel like life repeatedly presents us with the same lessons until we finally learn them. How many days have you spent worrying and stressing about the things you cannot control? What has it gotten you?
.
I invite you to try something new.
.
🥀 How will you practice this today?🥀
.

✨Be still, my uterus…✨

🍂 Life lately…🍂
.
When’s the last time you had expectations of something that were smashed completely to smithereens AND YET you find yourself completely ok with it? For me it was the foolhardy idea I had 5 months ago that I was going to “hit the ground running” after I had my son and get right back to work on creating content. Hilarious. 
.
I do plan on coming back but I dont think that things will look the way they used to around here on my social medias. In the past couple years I have changed SO much as a person and my recent cancer scare has only served to solidify those changes…and in my opinion…for the better. 
.
Life is slower…sweeter…and more intentional these days and I’m all the way here for It.
.
🍂 talk soon xo 🍂

1. Fall is showing up in all her glory in TN

6. I started making my own bone broths and home remedies like fire cider and fermented garlic

🎃 Hope everyone’s having a swell spooky season
